Makami refers to the deification of the wolves (Japanese wolves) that once lived in Japan. Since ancient times, Makami has been worshiped as a [[sacred beast]]. It was considered a protector of [[:en:crops|crops]] against [[:en:wild boars|boars]] and [[:en:Deer|Deer]], capable of understanding human speech, discerning human [[:en:Nature|Nature]], guarding good people, and punishing [[:en:Evil|Evil]] ones. Makami was also believed to provide [[:en:protection|protection]] against [[:en:misfortune|misfortune]], particularly [[:en:Fire|fires]] and [[theft]], and was often depicted on [[:en:Ema|Ema]] (votive plaques){{sfn|Shogakukan|2020|p=Makami}}.
