{{Infobox deity}}{{afc comment|Wikidata entry [[Category:Has wikidata]][[d:Q2349235]] Wikidata name: [[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 10:37, 11 June 2025 (UTC)}} {{Otheruses|Wolf deified in Japanese mythology|A place name in Mimasaka City, Okayama Prefecture|Fukumoto Village}} '''Makami''' (真神{{sfn|Matsumura|2020|p=Makami}}, まがみ{{sfn|Matsumura|2020|p=Makami}}, しんじん{{sfn|Shogakukan|2020|p=Makami}}) refers to the [[:en:Japanese wolf|wolf]] (ニホンオオカミ) as its [[ancient name]] or [[alternative name]]{{sfn|Matsumura|2020|p=Makami}}{{sfn|Shogakukan|2020|p=Makami}}, meaning "true [[:en:God|God]]" or "righteous god"{{sfn|Shogakukan|2020|p=Makami}}. It is also known as "'''Ōkuchi no Makami''' (大口真神)" and "'''Sacred Dog''' (御神犬)".
